description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SOUTH WORCESTER Home Treatment Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SENIOR HOME TREATMENT CLINICIAN RMN/SW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full and part time vacancies available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are pleased to be able to advertise the above Band 6 posts in the South Worcester Home Treatment Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work with people who are in an acute episode of a mental illness, providing intensive treatment and support in their own home, to avoid the need for hospital admission. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will convey in their application and at interview that he/she is highly motivated by clinical work and be able to relate experience which he/she has that can be of use in this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who can demonstrate the ability to work alongside patients finding innovative ways to engage people in life and recovery.  Positive risk management is vital to the provision of Home Treatment.  Working collaboratively with immediate colleagues, other teams and agencies is also an essential part of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be a team player and able to work independently.  You will be joining a skilled and experienced group of staff, which will give you opportunities to learn through joint working and more formal learning opportunities. Regular supervision and appraisal will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use of a car for work (due to the rural geography of Worcestershire) and ability to work shifts are essential to this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information regarding these posts please contact: Karen Hardwick or Ellie Gibbs, Home Treatment Team Leaders, on 01905 681697&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
